This commands are necessary to creat a new modul

  % cd ../yast2/modules/y2c_skeleton

  % make_new_module <new-name> <maintainer> <email>



Example
  % make_new_module adsl "Michael Hager" mike@suse.de

Now, the new modul "y2c_adsl" was created in ../yast2/modules.


To create the corresponing translation module, do this steps:
   % cd ../yast2/po/y2t_skeleton
                 ^^
   % make_new_module <new-name> <maintainer> <email>



----------------------------------------------------------

Just now, you can easily check in,
because there are no generated files

   % cvs add y2c_<new-name>
   % cd y2c_<new-name>
   % cvs add * 
   % cvs add src/* package/* doc/*
   % cvs ci  CO* M* R* V* c* m* y* src/*.ycp src/*.am package/y* doc/M*
   % cvs ci y2c_<new-name>

----------------------------------------------------------

To test the "default features", please type:

make -f Makefile.cvs
make
sudo make install

/usr/lib/YaST2/bin/y2qt menu '(.test)' qt -geometry 640x480 -style=platinum


----------------------------------------------------------
----------------------------------------------------------
Attention:
----------------------------------------------------------
You have to modify the spec file "modules/y2c_<name>/y2c_<name>.spec.in"
if there are package dependencies, or new files ... 


----------------------------------------------------------
----------------------------------------------------------
I you want to enhance this skelleton:
----------------------------------------------------------

The make_new_modul script expand the following variables:

rc_config :        packagename   adsl
Michael Hager   maintainer    "Michael Hager"
mike@suse.de        email         mike@suse.de
XXdataX          date          "Wed Jul  5 09:15:24 CEST 2000"
